# --- OS / editor cruft ---
.DS_Store
__MACOSX/
*.swp
.obsidian/workspace*
.obsidian/cache
.vscode/

# --- Secrets (NEVER commit) ---
# Excludes .env at any depth (e.g. Expansions/<slug>/.env). Keys-only
# templates are kept tracked via the negation below.
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
# ...but always ship the keys-only example template:
!.env.example
!**/.env.example
# Local MCP server configs may embed credentials — never commit:
.mcp.json
**/.mcp.json
.cursor/mcp.json
# Private keys / certs:
*.key
*.pem
id_rsa
# BUILD-002 WP1 (FU-1): the pinned Supabase pooler CA is a PUBLIC certificate
# (a trust anchor, not a secret) and is deliberately committed. Guards:
# test/tlsTransportGuards.test.js fails if a PRIVATE KEY block ever appears in
# it, and scripts/secret-scan.sh flags PEM private-key blocks repo-wide.
!services/fusion-capture-gateway/certs/supabase-pooler-ca.pem

# --- Derived database mirror & SQLite sidecars ---
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
# ...except: ship a prebuilt root mypka.db as a no-Python fallback, so a
# machine with no working Python/PyYAML can still run the Cockpit via
# `git pull` alone (see start-cockpit.ps1/.sh). It stays regenerable/
# overwritable by scripts/regen-mypka-db.py wherever Python IS available.
!/mypka.db

# --- Agent-skills junction layer (machine-local) ---
# `npx skills add` installs skill content into .agents/skills/ (tracked) and
# creates Windows junctions under .claude/skills/ pointing at it. With
# core.symlinks=false git would commit the junction CONTENTS as a duplicate
# copy of the pack — so the junction layer stays local; regenerate with
# `npx skills add supabase/agent-skills`.
.claude/skills/supabase/
.claude/skills/supabase-postgres-best-practices/

# --- Dependencies & build artifacts ---
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.next/
.cache/
*.tsbuildinfo
# Portable Node.js the Windows launcher may bootstrap on machines with no
# admin rights and no Node on PATH (start-cockpit.ps1) - local, removable cache:
.node-portable/

# --- Logs & runtime state ---
*.log
logs/
tmp/
*.pid

# --- Private/local Warwick context while this repository is public ---
# Keep personal journal and current-context material local during the
# myPKA/Fusion247Brain merge and testing phase. Public architecture docs may
# describe the mechanism, but personal evidence belongs in the local/private
# PKM layer unless Warwick explicitly approves publication for that change.
PKM/Journal/
PKM/My Life/Current Context/
PKM/My Life/About Warwick/
# BUILD-002 governed capture inbox: raw personal captures land here from the
# live gateway (Telegram → Brain). Personal evidence — never published from
# the public repo (same doctrine as PKM/Journal above).
Team Inbox/captures/

# --- Local immutable external-source payloads ---
# Keep the register and rules public, but do not publish captured transcripts,
# PDFs, uploads, or other raw external-source payloads from the public repo.
/Sources (Immutable)/**
!/Sources (Immutable)/
!/Sources (Immutable)/INDEX.md
!/Sources (Immutable)/README.md
